$\begin{align}
\int_0^2 -8y^2 \, dy &= \left[ \dfrac{-8y^3}{3} \right]_0^2 \\ \\
&= \dfrac{-8(2)^3}{3} - \dfrac{-8(0)}{3} \\ \\
&= \dfrac{-64}{3}
\end{align}$

Second, we evaluate the outer integral.

$\begin{align}
\int_0^2 \dfrac{y}{2} - 2y^{2.5} - \dfrac{1}{2} + 2y^2 \, dy &= \left[ \dfrac{y^2}{4} - \dfrac{2y^{3.5}}{3.5} - \dfrac{y}{2} + \dfrac{2y^3}{3} \right]_0^2 \\ \\
&= 1 - \dfrac{32 \sqrt{2}}{7} - 1 + \dfrac{16}{3} \\ \\
&= \dfrac{16}{3} - \dfrac{32 \sqrt{2}}{7}
\end{align}$

Second, we evaluate the outer integral.

$\begin{align}
\int_1^3 4\sqrt{y} \, dy &= 4 \left[ \dfrac{y^{1.5}}{1.5} \right]_1^3 \\ \\
&= 4 \left( \dfrac{6 \sqrt{3}}{3}  - \dfrac{2}{3} \right) \\ \\
&= 8\sqrt{3} - \dfrac{8}{3}
\end{align}$

Second, we evaluate the outer integral.

$\begin{align}
\int_0^1 2y^3 - \dfrac{3y^4}{2} \, dy &= \left[ \dfrac{y^4}{2} - \dfrac{3y^5}{10} \right]_0^1 \\ \\
&= \dfrac{1}{2} - \dfrac{3}{10} \\ \\
&= \dfrac{1}{5}
\end{align}$

Second, we evaluate the outer integral.

$\begin{align}
\int_{-1}^1 x^3  + \dfrac{3x^4}{2} \, dx &= \left[ \dfrac{x^4}{4} + \dfrac{3x^5}{10} \right]_{-1}^1 \\ \\
&= \dfrac{1}{4} + \dfrac{3}{10} - \left( \dfrac{1}{4} - \dfrac{3}{10} \right) \\ \\
&= \dfrac{3}{5}
\end{align}$
